  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed roof extension by reason of its inappropriate design, scale, siting form, massing, bulk and form would from a dominant and discordant addition to the host locally listed property and wider terrace setting. The addition would be visible from surrounding public and private realms and views within the Conservation Area. It would therefore be unacceptable in principle, as it would visually disrupt the existing unaltered and rhythmic roofscape within the terrace. The proposal is contrary to the NPPF (2021), Policies D1, D4 and HC1 of the London Plan (2021), Policies CS8 and CS9 of the Islington Core Strategy (2011), Policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of the Development Management Policies (2013), the guidance contained within the Urban Design Guide (2017) and the Arlington Square Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002)."
